6. 固有値問題(Eigen decomposition)¶

\begin{equation*} x_i=(x_i1,...x_id)^{\mathrm{T}}(i = 1,...,N) \end{equation*}

N $X=(x_1,...x_N)^{\mathrm{T}}$ $\bar{x}=(\bar{x_1}...,\bar{x_d})^{\mathrm{T}}$
$\bar{X}=(x_1 - \bar{x}....,x_N - \bar{x})^{\mathrm{T}}$ \begin{equation*} \sum = Var\{\bar{X}\} = \frac{1}{N}\bar{X}^{\mathrm{T}}\bar{X}\ \end{equation*}

N $x_i - \bar{x}$ \begin{equation*} a_j=(a_{j1}...a_{jd})^{\mathrm{T}}(j = 1....,d) \end{equation*} \begin{equation*} s_j = (s_{1j},....s_{Nj})^{\mathrm{T}} = \bar{Xa}_j \end{equation*}

$s_{1j},....s_{Nj}$ 0

\begin{equation*} Var\{{s_j}\} = \frac{1}{N}{s}_j^Ts_j = \frac{1}{N}(\bar{Xa}_j)^{\mathrm{T}}(\bar{Xa}_j) = \frac{1}{N}{a}_j^T\bar{X}^{\mathrm{T}}\bar{Xa}_j = a_j^TVar\{{\bar{X}\}}a_j \end{equation*}

$a_j$1 \begin{equation*} E(a_j) = a_j^TVar\{{\bar{X}\}}a_j - \lambda(a_j^T - 1) \end{equation*} $a_j$

$a_j$ 0 \begin{equation*} \frac{\partial E(a_j)}{\partial a_j} = 2Var{{\bar{X}}}a_j - 2\lambda a_j = 0 (1) \end{equation*}

$Var \{\bar{X}\}a_j = \lambda a_j$


$a_j$

(1)$\lambda_1\geq...\geq\lambda_d$ $a_1,...,a_d$

-QR

(SVD)
$np$ X \begin{equation*} X = UV^T = (u_1 u_2 ... u_p) \left( \begin{array}{cccc} \sqrt{_1} & 0 & \ldots & 0 \\ 0 & \sqrt{_2} & \ldots & 0 \\ \vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\ 0 & 0 & \ldots & \sqrt{_p} \end{array} \right) \left( \begin{array}{cccc} \upsilon^T_1 \\ \upsilon^T_2 \\ \vdots \\ \upsilon^T_p \end{array} \right) \end{equation*}

$U$ $XX^T$ $np$
$V$ $X^TX$ $pp$

$\Lambda$ $XX^T$ $X^TX$ $12...p$
$pp$

$np$ $X$
$p$$n$
$X^TX$ $_i$ $_i$

$X=UV^T$ $XV=U$ \begin{equation*} (X\upsilon _1 \ \ X\upsilon _2 \ \ ... \ \ X\upsilon _p) = (\sqrt{\lambda _1 u_1} \ \ \sqrt{\lambda _2 u_2} \ \ ... \ \ \sqrt{\lambda _p u_p}) \end{equation*}

$1$ $\sqrt{\lambda_1u_1}$ \begin{equation*} Var\{{X_\upsilon{_1}}\} = (X_\upsilon{_1})^{\mathrm{T}}(X_\upsilon{_1}) = \left( \sqrt{\lambda _1 u_1} \right)^{\mathrm{T}}\left( \sqrt{\lambda _1 u_1} \right) = \lambda_1 \end{equation*}

1
1 $q(p)$ $i$ \begin{equation*} \tilde{V} = (\upsilon_1 \ \ ... \upsilon_q) \end{equation*}

$X$ $X\tilde{V}$ \begin{equation*} Var{\{X\tilde{V}\}} = (X\tilde{V})^{\mathrm{T}}(X\tilde{V}) = \tilde{V}^{\mathrm{T}}X^{\mathrm{T}}X\tilde{V} = \tilde{V}^{\mathrm{T}}V\Lambda^{\mathrm{T}}U^{\mathrm{T}}U\Lambda\tilde{V}^{\mathrm{T}}\tilde{V} \\ = \tilde{V}^{\mathrm{T}}V\Lambda^{\mathrm{2}}V^{\mathrm{T}}\tilde{V} \end{equation*}

$\tilde{V}^{\mathrm{T}}V$ \begin{equation*} \tilde{V}^{\mathrm{T}}V = \left( \begin{array}{cccc} \upsilon^T_1 \\ \vdots \\ \upsilon^T_q \end{array} \right) \ \ (\upsilon_1 \ \ ... \upsilon_q) = \left( \begin{array}{cccc} 1 & 0 & \ldots & 0 & 0 & \ldots & 0 \\ 0 & 1 & \ldots & 0 & 0 & \ldots & 0 \\ \vdots & \ddots & \ddots & 0 & \vdots & \vdots & \vdots \\ 0 & \ldots & 0 & 1 & 0 & \ldots & 0 \end{array} \right) \end{equation*} \begin{equation*} Var\{X\tilde{V}\} = \lambda^2_q \end{equation*}

def draw_face_compressed(img, ndim):
    A = np.dot((face_01 - pca.mean_), pca.components_.T[:, :ndim])
    A_inv = pca.components_.T[:, :ndim].dot(A) + pca.mean_
    return A_inv

image_shape = (64,64)
face_01 = oliv.images[0].reshape(-1)

def show_compressed(img, n_dim):
    n_dim = 3
    face_compressed = draw_face_compressed(img, n_dim)
    plt.imshow(face_compressed.reshape(image_shape), cmap=plt.cm.gray)
    print("", pca.explained_variance_ratio_)
